<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-subscribers" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-bugs" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

      <div>
        <img alt="" src="/@@/question" />
        <a tal:attributes="href context/fmt:url" tal:content="context/title" />
      </div>

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">

    <h1 i18n:translate=""
        metal:fill-slot="heading">Link question to a bug report</h1>

    <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
      <p i18n:translate="">Enter the number or nickname of the Launchpad bug report
        that should be linked to question #<tal:id i18n:name="id" replace="context/id" />
        &ldquo;<tal:title i18n:name="title" replace="context/title"/>&rdquo;.
      </p>

      <p i18n:translate="">If you don't know the bug number, you can search for it
        on the <a href=""
                  tal:attributes="href string:${context/target/fmt:url}/+bugs"
                  >Bug listing</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>You can link a bug to a question. You should do this, if the problem
    described in the question is related
    to a bug already filed. The link to the bug report will appear on the
    question page, and a link to the question will appear on
    the target bug page.
  </p>
  <p>You need to know the bug number that you want to link to. You will
    probably want to use the search page to locate the bug, if you don't
    know its ID.
  </p>
</metal:help>
</body>
</html>

